name: College Football Championship Game (Canceled)
blurb: We are making the finest college football video game known to man, coming to X360 and PS3 in 2014 -- and we want you to help design it.

rewards.reward: Kick Major Publisher Butt: This level is for those who are just tired of the huge publishers running franchises into the ground! Every backer at all levels receives a Kickstarter Backer Badge on the Longshot Games Forums. We invite you to our forums to discuss the College Football Championship game and to interact with other avid football fans
First Down: Xbox Live Arcade or PSN (your choice) download of College Football Championship 2014. This limited price is only available to the first 1000 backers, so sign up now!

Second Down: Xbox Live Arcade or PSN download of College Football Championship 2014. If you miss out on being a First Down backer, this is still a great deal. This limited price is only available to the first 25,000 backers.
Touchdown: Regularly priced Xbox Live Arcade or PSN download of College Football Championship 2014.

Developer Mode: At this level, you receive a copy of the game through XBox Live Arcade or PSN and are granted access to our internal developer forums, where you will have a hands-on look at how the game is being developed, and will be able to post your own ideas and designs for the game and get responses and feedback. A pre-order of the game is included at this level.

Developer Mode Plus: In addition to everything in Developer Mode, you will also receive the official developer team T-shirt, the same ones that the programmers and artists at Longshot Games get. Wear it with pride!
Three-Star Recruit: Your name will be added to the pool of names for randomly generated three-star recruits in the game. You will also receive everything at the Developer Mode Plus level.
Four-Star Recruit: Your name will be added to the pool of names for randomly generated four-star recruits in the game. You will also receive everything at the Developer Mode Plus level.

Five-Star Recruit: Not only do we have your name on a five-star recruit in the game, but at this level only, we will put your face in the game to go along with it. Just take some pictures according to the instructions we send you and you'll be in the game. (This is optional.) You also receive everything at the Developer Mode Plus level.

Launch Party: You will be an honored guest at our launch party in Austin, Texas. You may also invite up to three others. Travel not included at this level. You also receive everything at the Five-Star Recruit level.

Local Advertising: At this level, you will be able to send us a billboard advertisement to be used in one in-game stadium of your choice. There will be six slots in each stadium - if more than six companies choose this level for any particular stadium, we will rotate the advertisements for each game. (You may choose to have your money refunded if you do not wish to have your ad rotated.) Longshot Games reserves the right to reject any advertisement based on content, and will not accept advertisements for alcohol, tobacco, or pornography.

Launch Party With Travel: You will be an honored guest at our launch party in Austin, Texas, with first-class plane tickets provided from anywhere in the contiguous United States for you and one other person of your choice.

National Advertising: Each stadium will have six billboards displaying advertisements (separate from the Local Advertising boards above). At this level, you may place your advertisement on one of these boards, which will display in every game played in College Football Championship. The same caveats as in Local Advertising with regards to rotating ads and acceptable ad content apply.
